: Wenceslau Guimarães, 
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E925E773CFC3BFF4FFBD1BCF3" box="[965,1088,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="167">Bacci 273</emphasis>
(
<collectionCode id="ED18AE49925E773CFBA7FF4EFB2DBCF3" box="[1113,1212,158,184]" country="Brazil" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15526" name="CEPEC, CEPLAC" pageId="14" pageNumber="167" type="Herbarium">CEPEC</collectionCode>
!); 
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E925E773CFB23FF4EFA3ABCF3" box="[1245,1451,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="167">Goldenberg 1756</emphasis>
(
<collectionCode id="ED18AE49925E773CFF6EFF12FF62BC97" box="[144,243,194,220]" country="Brazil" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15526" name="CEPEC, CEPLAC" pageId="14" pageNumber="167" type="Herbarium">CEPEC</collectionCode>
!); 
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E925E773CFEF4FF12FE33BC97" box="[266,418,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="167">Thomas 9285</emphasis>
(
<collectionCode id="ED18AE49925E773CFE4FFF12FD83BC97" box="[433,530,194,220]" country="Brazil" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15526" name="CEPEC, CEPLAC" pageId="14" pageNumber="167" type="Herbarium">CEPEC</collectionCode>
!, 
<collectionCode id="ED18AE49925E773CFDDEFF13FDD9BC96" box="[544,584,195,221]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15556" name="William and Lynda Steere Herbarium of the New York Botanical Garden" pageId="14" pageNumber="167" type="Herbarium">NY</collectionCode>
, 
<collectionCode id="ED18AE49925E773CFDADFF12FD10BC97" box="[595,641,194,220]" country="Brazil" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15528" name="Jardim Botânico do Rio de Janeiro" pageId="14" pageNumber="167" type="Herbarium">RB</collectionCode>
!).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB6368C925E773CFF43FF36FDC9BD03" blockId="14.[136,1452,158,761]" pageId="14" pageNumber="167">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E925E773CFF43FF36FE51BD4B" bold="true" box="[189,448,230,256]" pageId="14" pageNumber="167">Conservation Status:</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E925E773CFE3FFF36FD78BD4B" box="[449,745,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="167">
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F925E773CFE20FF36FD78BD4B" box="[478,745,230,256]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="14" pageNumber="167" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirsutissima">Bertolonia hirsutissima</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
occurs inside the “Estação Ecológica Estadual Wenceslau Guimarães”. The species has an EOO of 
<quantity id="4CF19B69925E773CFDB8FEDBFDECBD6C" box="[582,637,267,295]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="167" unit="km" value="7.0">7 km</quantity>
² and AOO of 
<quantity id="4CF19B69925E773CFCEBFEDAFCCDBD6C" box="[789,860,266,295]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="14" pageNumber="167" unit="km" value="15.0">15 km</quantity>
², and should be classified as “Critically Endangered” (CR), following 
<bibRefCitation id="EF984B7D925E773CFEBCFEFEFE49BD03" author="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee &amp; Cambridge, UK" box="[322,472,302,328]" pageId="14" pageNumber="167" refId="ref19879" refString="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee (2017) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 13 (March 2017). Prepared by the IUCN species survival commission. IUCN Council, Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK, 108 pp. Available from: http: // cmsdocs. s 3. amazonaws. com / RedList Guidelines. pdf (Accessed 9 February 2019)" type="book" year="2017">IUCN (2017)</bibRefCitation>
categories.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3136507925E773CFF43FE82FC80BEB3" pageId="14" pageNumber="167" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB6368C925E773CFF43FE82FC80BEB3" blockId="14.[136,1452,158,761]" pageId="14" pageNumber="167">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E925E773CFF43FE82FE98BD27" bold="true" box="[189,265,338,364]" pageId="14" pageNumber="167">Notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F925E773CFED8FE82FDBCBD27" box="[294,557,338,364]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="14" pageNumber="167" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirsutissima">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E925E773CFED8FE82FDBCBD27" box="[294,557,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="167">Bertolonia hirsutissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to 
<collectingRegion id="49CDF86E925E773CFD33FE82FC80BD27" box="[717,785,338,364]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="14" pageNumber="167">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, occurring in montane rainforests (
<figureCitation id="13322A09925E773CFB6BFE82FB73BD26" box="[1173,1250,338,365]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[136,229,1949,1971]" captionTargetBox="[341,1239,654,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-255@5.[340,1247,641,1924]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Distributions of species of Bertolonia in Bahia.A. Bertolonia alternifolia. B. Bertolonia angustipetala. C. Bertolonia bullata. D. Bertolonia carmoi. E. Bertolonia cuspidata. F. Bertolonia hirsutissima. G. Bertolonia igrapiuna. H. Bertolonia kollmannii." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6597686" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6597686/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="167">Fig. 3f</figureCitation>
) on rocky, shaded and wet stone walls. Collected with flowers in January and December, and fruits in April. The species is characterized by the widely elliptic to ovate leaf blades with bullate surfaces and petioles densely glandulose-pilose (trichomes 
<quantity id="4CF19B69925E773CFA7FFE4AFF25BD92" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="167" unit="mm" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3–5 mm</quantity>
long). It also has petals with an apiculate apex ending in a caducous glandular head and anthers dehiscing through an extrorse pore. It is sympatric to 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F925E773CFDE9FE33FC0EBDB7" authority="Bacci &amp; Michelangeli" authorityName="Bacci &amp; Michelangeli" box="[535,927,482,508]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="14" pageNumber="167" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="reginatoi">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E925E773CFDE9FE33FD0CBDB7" box="[535,669,483,508]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="167">B. reginatoi</emphasis>
Bacci &amp; Michelangeli
</taxonomicName>
(in 
<bibRefCitation id="EF984B7D925E773CFC30FE32FB5ABDB7" author="Bacci, L. F. &amp; Amorim, A. M. &amp; Michelangeli, F. A. &amp; Goldenberg, R." box="[974,1227,482,509]" pageId="14" pageNumber="167" pagination="767 - 792" refId="ref18533" refString="Bacci, L. F., Amorim, A. M., Michelangeli, F. A. &amp; Goldenberg, R. (2018) Increased Sampling in Under-Collected Areas Sheds New Light on the Diversity and Distribution of Bertolonia, an Atlantic Forest Endemic Genus. Systematic Botany 43 (3): 767 - 792. https: // doi. org / 10.1600 / 036364418 X 697490" type="journal article" year="2018">
Bacci 
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E925E773CFBE8FE33FBD8BDB7" box="[1046,1097,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="167">et al</emphasis>
. 2018: 783
</bibRefCitation>
) and both share the wide ovate to cordiform leaf blades, petioles and abaxial leaf surfaces densely glandulose-punctate, and flowers with a light green hypanthium and pink petals. 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F925E773CFD97FDFAFCEBBE0F" box="[617,890,554,580]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="14" pageNumber="167" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirsutissima">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E925E773CFD97FDFAFCEBBE0F" box="[617,890,554,580]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="167">Bertolonia hirsutissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F925E773CFBECFDFBFB09BE0F" box="[1042,1176,555,580]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="14" pageNumber="167" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="reginatoi">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E925E773CFBECFDFBFB09BE0F" box="[1042,1176,555,580]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="167">B. reginatoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the bullate/foveolate leaf surfaces (
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E925E773CFEDBFD9FFEADBE23" box="[293,316,591,616]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="167">vs</emphasis>
. flat in 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F925E773CFE6AFD9FFD88BE23" box="[404,537,591,616]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="14" pageNumber="167" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="reginatoi">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E925E773CFE6AFD9FFD88BE23" box="[404,537,591,616]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="167">B. reginatoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), hypanthium only glandulose-punctate (
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E925E773CFC16FD9FFC6EBE23" box="[1000,1023,591,616]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="167">vs</emphasis>
. hypanthium glandulose-punctate and glandulose-villose) and anthers dehiscing through an extrorse pore (
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E925E773CFC7CFDA3FC08BEC7" box="[898,921,627,652]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="167">vs</emphasis>
. introrse). In the state of 
<collectingRegion id="49CDF86E925E773CFB4AFDA2FB69BEC7" box="[1204,1272,626,652]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="14" pageNumber="167">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F925E773CFAFDFDA3FA3ABEC7" box="[1283,1451,626,652]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="14" pageNumber="167" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hirsutissima">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E925E773CFAFDFDA3FA3ABEC7" box="[1283,1451,626,652]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="167">B. hirsutissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have the same bullate/foveolate leaf blades as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F925E773CFD43FD47FCBFBEFB" box="[701,814,662,688]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="14" pageNumber="167" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bullata">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E925E773CFD43FD47FCBFBEFB" box="[701,814,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="167">B. bullata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F925E773CFC97FD47FB93BEFB" box="[873,1026,662,688]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="14" pageNumber="167" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kollmannii">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E925E773CFC97FD47FB93BEFB" box="[873,1026,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="167">B. kollmannii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. From these, it differs mainly by the broader leaf blades, flowers with the hypanthium only glandulose-punctate and anthers dehiscing through an extrorse pore. For more details see Bacci 
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E925E773CFE06FD0FFDB8BEB3" box="[504,553,734,760]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="167">et al</emphasis>
. (2016) and 
<tableCitation id="C68B0337925E773CFD49FD0EFC9ABEB3" box="[695,779,734,760]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="6.[136,224,623,649]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="TABLE 1. Selected morphological characters scored for species in Bertolonia that occur in the state of Bahia, Brazil. “GP”= Glandulose-punctate; “GV”= Glandulose-villose." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF76660492567734FF76FDBFF843BEC2" pageId="14" pageNumber="167" tableUuid="DF76660492567734FF76FDBFF843BEC2">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
